 Lippmann's work helps to clarify one of the most pressing predicaments of American democracy today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFreedom of the press. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh1 aBlumenthal, Sidney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlumenthal, Sidney.1 aSteel, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteel, Ronald.1 aWilentz, Sean.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400824496zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400824496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400824496.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK